div.span: 1. When project monitoring is enabled, Prometheus monitors the state of each workload in a single project. No state data is collected from other clusters or projects. In this diagram, Promtheus is monitoring the workloads in Project A: HTTP Workload A and TCP/UPD Workload A.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 178px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.span: 2. After Prometheus stores your workload state data, you can view it from the instance of Grafana deployed with Prometheus. Project metrics cannot be viewed from the Rancher UI, only Grafana.
